type: software
title: "A Hand For A Game: Real-time Hand Gesture Recognition and the resBalancer Engine for Gaming Applications"
abstract: >-
  An experimental computer vision system for real-time hand gesture recognition in gaming, featuring the custom resBalancer engine for adaptive frame processing and performance optimization. The system uses MediaPipe for hand landmark detection and implements custom gesture interpretation algorithms, with a C++/CUDA backend for high performance. This is a personal research project with author-specific calibrations and is not intended for general accessibility use or production deployment.

