# Research and academic context
research-context:
  research-question: "Can single-hand gesture recognition and adaptive frame processing (resBalancer) provide viable gaming control without physical input devices?"
  methodology: "Computer vision-based gesture detection using MediaPipe landmarks, custom interpretation algorithms, and adaptive C++/CUDA frame processing (resBalancer)"
  target-environment: "Windows gaming applications with real-time performance requirements"
  limitations: "Author-specific calibration, right-hand detection only, hardware-dependent performance"

